                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I didn't see this anywhere else, if it is well just ignore me, everyone else does, including my wife and especially my 5 month old son <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
1)  Go to your starting city.  As soon as you zone in, a scripted text will pop up telling you, who you should talk to in your city.
<br />

<br />
2)  Once you track down that NPC, do the usual stuff in regards to getting information (i.e. the stuff in brackets).  After a bit you'll be told to go to 1 of 5 NPCs.  I'm just going to give you information on 1:   Barste Songweaver, East Commons Tunnel near the Shaddy Swashbuckler.
<br />

<br />
3)  Go to EC and hail Barste Songweaver (name might be mispelled).  He'll ask you questions based on the information you were told in step 2.  It should be to hard.
<br />

<br />
4)  You'll be given a greenish stone, that is actually a augmention for any charm.  If you were like me, you added it to your PoP Charm.  Now your probably wondering:  Ok so Najib, how do I add that to my PoP Charm ....  my response:  Hold your horses, I haven't got that far yet.
<br />

<br />
5)  Hail one of the NPCs, near Songweaver, Miragul or something.  You want to find the one that will Translocate you.  You'll know this because you'll see 5 zones in brackets.  Say:  South Ro
<br />

<br />
6)  One you in the camp in South Ro, move around to behind one of the tents.  You'll see a table with water in it.  Left Click that, which will open a two slot window with a combine button (just like a Forge).  Put your charm and the stone in it and hit combine.  Now you have an augmented Charm.  
<br />

<br />
So now your probably wondering:  Ok so, how do I get into an adventure.... Well if you weren't so impatient, I would tell you.
<br />

<br />
A)  Get a group or a raid.  4 is the mininium I believe.
<br />
B)  Go to one of the camps and speak to one of the NPCs with (Adventurer Recruiter) under his/her/its name.  Now Right Click on that guy and a window will pop up.  Here you can request an adventure.  
<br />
C)  You have 30 minutes to get to the dungeon, so don't accept an adventure until your group/raid is ready.
<br />
D)  Go forth and seek your fortune.
<br />

<br />
Tips that I have learned so far:
<br />

<br />
1)  Don't listen to anyone you are not familar with in regards to KEI/Tranq/VoQ.  If they say they already got it, tell them to click it off and cast your version.  If the refuse, polietly remind them you will not be recasting KEI/Tranq/VoQ while in the dungeon unless they happen to dispelled.  Why?  Its to much damn mana.  My first adventure was in Deepest Guk, all 65's.  We didn't sit down to med except for a 3 minute break and we beat the dungeon with 1 minute to spare.  I was slowing and mezzing.  Biggest pull was 5, all pulls where at least 2+ with the except for 1 or 2.  I had to cast Tranq while in the dungeon twice because 2 people told me that they had "just" gotten VoQ and yet 30 minutes into the dungeon it was fading.  I had to use GM about 45 minutes into the adventure.  
<br />

<br />
2)  Don't be afraid to mez pull while the group is fighting.  I did this towards the end of the dungeon and if I hadn't I don't think we would have passed.  I pulled at least 15 mobs (not at once) by creeping up, targeting a mob and mezzing it.  Its friends would come (1 or 2) and I would bring them to the camp.  I think all but one time, the mem blur off of Apathy worked and the mez wore off but the mob didn't come after me.
<br />

<br />
I think that's about all I can really think of atm.  I'm sure I haven't told anyone that they already don't know, just was a little bored at work and thought I would post.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
